<div>Hi,</div><br><div>I'm experiencing system-wide freezes (10-15 second=
s, then recovery) with an</div><div>Intel BE202 160MHz card when under su=
stained network throughput. The issue</div><div>is specific to the iwlmld=
 op=5Fmode loaded with firmware 97+. The older</div><div>iwlmvm op=5Fmode=
 with firmware 92 on kernel 6.12 LTS is completely stable</div><div>under=
 identical workloads.</div><br><div>Hardware:</div><div>&nbsp; Intel Wi-=46=
i 7 BE202 160MHz =5B8086:272b=5D (rev 1a)</div><div>&nbsp; Subsystem: =5B=
8086:02f4=5D Misty Peak</div><div>&nbsp; Board: ASUS ROG STRIX Z790-=46 G=
AMING WI=46I II</div><br><div>Affected:</div><div>&nbsp; Kernel: 6.18.8-a=
rch2-1 (also tested 6.18.9-2-cachyos =E2=80=94 same result)</div><div>&nb=
sp; =46irmware: 101.6ef20b19.0 gl-c0-fm-c0-101.ucode</div><div>&nbsp; Op =
mode: iwlmld</div><br><div>Not affected:</div><div>&nbsp; Kernel: 6.12.69=
-2-cachyos-lts</div><div>&nbsp; =46irmware: 92.67ce4588.0 gl-c0-fm-c0-92.=
ucode</div><div>&nbsp; Op mode: iwlmvm</div><br><div>Reproduction:</div><=
div>&nbsp; Run 4 parallel large downloads + GitLab CI runners:</div><div>=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; curl -o /dev/null http://speedtest.tele2.net/100GB.zip=
 &amp;</div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; curl -o /dev/null http://speedtest.te=
le2.net/100GB.zip &amp;</div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; curl -o /dev/null ht=
tp://speedtest.tele2.net/100GB.zip &amp;</div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; cur=
l -o /dev/null http://speedtest.tele2.net/100GB.zip &amp;</div><div>&nbsp=
; System freezes within minutes (mouse, keyboard, desktop all unresponsiv=
e</div><div>&nbsp; for 10-15 seconds, then recovers).</div><br><div>Kerne=
l log during freeze:</div><div>&nbsp; iwlwifi 0000:07:00.0: fail to flush=
 all tx fifo queues Q 1</div><div>&nbsp; iwlwifi 0000:07:00.0: Queue 1 is=
 stuck 4 5</div><br><div>Secondary effect:</div><div>&nbsp; During the TX=
 queue stall, slab=5Funreclaimable spikes to =7E40 GB</div><div>&nbsp; (p=
age allocation failures at order:0 with G=46P=5FKERNEL=7C=5F=5FG=46P=5FNO=
MEMALLOC),</div><div>&nbsp; then recovers after the queue unsticks.</div>=
<br><div>Workarounds tried (none resolved the issue):</div><div>&nbsp; - =
options iwlwifi disable=5F11be=3D1</div><div>&nbsp; - options iwlwifi pow=
er=5Fsave=3D0</div><div>&nbsp; - ethtool -K wlan0 tso off gso off</div><d=
iv>&nbsp; - pcie=5Faspm=3Doff kernel parameter</div><div>&nbsp; - vm.min=5F=
free=5Fkbytes=3D1048576</div><br><div>The issue appears to be in the iwlm=
ld TX queue handling under sustained</div><div>throughput. On 6.12 LTS wi=
th firmware 92 (iwlmvm), the same workload</div><div>runs indefinitely wi=
thout any stalls.</div><br><div>Others are reporting the same issue:</div=
><div>&nbsp; https://github.com/CachyOS/linux-cachyos/issues/673</div><br=
><div>=46ull dmesg and ethtool output attached.</div><br><div>Thanks,</di=
v><div>Alp</div>
